<% content_for :title, "Data sources & methodology — tokenprice.fyi" %>
<% content_for :description, "Where every price on tokenprice.fyi comes from: provider pricing pages, Wayback Machine verification, a daily OpenRouter sync — every price point dated and sourced." %>
<% content_for :canonical, sources_url %>

<% content_for :head do %>
  <%= json_ld({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "WebPage",
        name: "Data sources & methodology",
        url: sources_url,
        description: "Where the pricing data on tokenprice.fyi comes from, how it is verified, and who deserves credit for it.",
        isPartOf: { "@type": "WebSite", name: "tokenprice.fyi", url: root_url }
      }) %>
<% end %>

<div class="sources-page">
  <%# ── Header ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
  <div class="sources-header">
    <h1 class="sources-h1">Where the numbers come from</h1>
    <p class="sources-subtitle">
      Every price is dated and sourced. This is the full ledger — which pages were
      read, how they were verified, and who gets credit.
    </p>
  </div>

  <%# ── Methodology ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
  <section class="sources-prose" aria-labelledby="sources-methodology">
    <h2 id="sources-methodology">Methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Prices here are an <strong>append-only history</strong>, not a number that gets
      overwritten. When a provider cuts a price, the old figure doesn't disappear —
      a new dated price point is appended next to it, and every point records the
      source it was read from. That source string is stored on the row itself and
      shown on each model's snapshot table.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Anthropic figures I curate by hand and will stand behind.</strong> Other
      providers are best-effort: read from their public pricing pages, cross-checked
      by a daily OpenRouter sync, and occasionally lagging. When something's wrong it
      gets fixed and noted, not silently overwritten.
    </p>
    <p>
      Historical points get a second pass. Each one is checked against
      <strong>Wayback Machine captures</strong> of the provider's pricing page from around
      its effective date — so the price recorded for March 2024 is the price an
      archived copy of the page actually showed in March 2024, not a number
      remembered later. Points that can only be dated approximately say so in
      their notes rather than pretending to precision.
    </p>
    <p>
      That pass turns up real corrections — cached-input rates and output prices
      seeded a notch off, and price cuts that had gone unrecorded — each now fixed
      against the archived page that showed it. It also leaves a few honest
      <strong>judgement calls</strong>, flagged in a point's note rather than hidden:
      a price whose value is confirmed but whose exact change date falls in a gap
      between captures is recorded as a <em>bracketed range</em>; a value
      corroborated only by secondary trackers — because the provider's own page
      archived as an empty, JavaScript-rendered shell — says so; and a small number
      of very recent or open-weight rates that no archived first-party page could
      confirm are kept but marked <em>unverified</em>, not dressed up as certain.
    </p>
  </section>

  <%# ── Stat row ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
  <div class="sources-stats">
    <div class="sources-stat">
      <span class="sources-stat-val num"><%= @price_point_count %></span>
      <span class="sources-stat-label">Price points</span>
    </div>
    <div class="sources-stat">
      <span class="sources-stat-val num"><%= @source_count %></span>
      <span class="sources-stat-label">Distinct sources</span>
    </div>
    <div class="sources-stat">
      <span class="sources-stat-val num"><%= @provider_count %></span>
      <span class="sources-stat-label">Providers covered</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# ── Attribution tables (live from the database) ────────────────────── %>
  <% @groups.each do |group| %>
    <section class="sources-group" aria-label="<%= group[:title] %>">
      <h2 class="sources-group-title"><%= group[:title] %></h2>
      <p class="sources-group-blurb"><%= group[:blurb] %></p>

      <div class="tp-card sources-table-wrap">
        <table class="sources-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Source</th>
              <th scope="col">Providers</th>
              <th scope="col" class="numeric">Models</th>
              <th scope="col" class="numeric">Price points</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <% group[:sources].each do |entry| %>
              <tr>
                <td class="sources-cell-source"><%= source_link(entry[:source]) %></td>
                <td class="sources-cell-providers"><%= entry[:providers].join(", ") %></td>
                <td class="numeric num"><%= entry[:models] %></td>
                <td class="numeric num"><%= entry[:price_points] %></td>
              </tr>
            <% end %>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>
  <% end %>

  <%# ── Acknowledgements ───────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
  <section class="sources-prose" aria-labelledby="sources-acknowledgements">
    <h2 id="sources-acknowledgements">Acknowledgements</h2>
    <p>This record stands on work other people do, and they should be credited for it:</p>
    <ul class="sources-ack-list">
      <li>
        <strong>The providers' own pricing pages</strong> — the first-party source
        for nearly every figure on this site. Each one is linked above, and on
        every price point it backs.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The Internet Archive's <%= link_to "Wayback Machine", "https://web.archive.org", class: "sources-link" %></strong>
        — historical prices are verified against its captures of provider pricing
        pages. Without the Archive there would be no checkable record of what
        these pages said in 2023.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong><%= link_to "OpenRouter", "https://openrouter.ai", class: "sources-link" %></strong>
        — a daily sync against its catalogue keeps current prices fresh across
        the long tail of models, and flags moves worth verifying first-party.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The <%= link_to "LiteLLM", "https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm", class: "sources-link" %> community pricing dataset</strong>
        — its version history is a map of <em>when</em> prices changed, used to
        discover historical changes worth backfilling. Discovery only: every
        change it surfaces is verified against an archived first-party page
        before it's recorded here.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If a price looks stale or wrong, the source is right there on the price
      point — check it, and <%= link_to "tell me", "mailto:chris@chrisgilbert.dev", class: "sources-link" %>.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
/* ── Sources page ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sources-page {
  max-width: 760px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 36px 0 60px;
}
.sources-header { margin-bottom: 28px; }
.sources-h1 {
  font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 44px);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.033em;
  line-height: 1.05;
  color: var(--color-slate-900);
}
.sources-subtitle {
  margin-top: 14px;
  max-width: 40em;
  color: var(--color-slate-500);
  font-size: 17px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* ── Prose sections ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sources-prose { margin-bottom: 36px; }
.sources-prose h2 {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--color-slate-900);
  margin-bottom: 14px;
}
.sources-prose p {
  font-size: 15.5px;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--color-slate-700);
  margin-bottom: 14px;
}
.sources-prose strong { color: var(--color-slate-900); }
.sources-ack-list { margin: 0 0 14px 20px; list-style: disc; }
.sources-ack-list li {
  font-size: 15.5px;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--color-slate-700);
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}
.sources-link {
  color: var(--color-slate-900);
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 3px;
  text-decoration-color: var(--color-slate-300);
}
.sources-link:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--color-slate-900); }

/* ── Stat row ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sources-stats {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 28px;
  margin-bottom: 36px;
  padding: 18px 22px;
  background: #fff;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-slate-200);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}
.sources-stat { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; }
.sources-stat-val {
  font-size: 24px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-slate-900);
}
.sources-stat-label {
  font-size: 11.5px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: .05em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-slate-400);
}

/* ── Attribution tables ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sources-group { margin-bottom: 36px; }
.sources-group-title {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--color-slate-900);
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.sources-group-blurb {
  font-size: 14.5px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--color-slate-500);
  margin-bottom: 14px;
  max-width: 44em;
}
.sources-table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; }
.sources-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; }
.sources-table thead th {
  background: var(--color-slate-50);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-slate-200);
  font-size: 11.5px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: .04em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--color-slate-400);
  padding: 11px 16px;
  text-align: left;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.sources-table tbody td {
  padding: 11px 16px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-slate-100);
  color: var(--color-slate-700);
  vertical-align: top;
}
.sources-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
.sources-table th.numeric, .sources-table td.numeric { text-align: right; }
.sources-cell-source { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; word-break: break-all; }
.sources-cell-providers { color: var(--color-slate-500); }

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .sources-stats { gap: 20px; }
}
</style>
